   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> represents the statistical response surface; 
 <italic class="italic">n</italic> stands for the number of observations in the training dataset; 
 <italic class="italic">x</italic>
 <sub class="sub">−
  <italic class="italic">j</italic>
 </sub> denotes all other variables (except for 
 <italic class="italic">x</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">j)</italic>
 </sub>. The estimated PDP of the predictor 
 <italic class="italic">x</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">j</italic>
 </sub> indicates the average value of the estimated response function 
 <inline-formula id="pone.0188033.e004" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pone.0188033.e004.jpg" id="pone.0188033.e004g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
